{
  "text": "The ASPP family consisting of three proteins (ASPP1, ASPP2 and iASPP) interacts with and modulates the functions of WT p53 [CITATION_1] . ASPP1/2 enhances p53-dependent cell death, whereas iASPP inhibits the apoptotic transactivation potential of p53 by direct interaction [CITATION_2] . Here, we review the oncogenic functions of iASPP in tumors and discuss promising therapeutic perspectives of miRNA, peptide and small molecules that reduce or block iASPP for the treatment of cancer.",
